2026-04-27| Valid Path in Grid with Street Types

Question
Return true if valid path exists, else false.
	Approach
1.	Define allowed directions for each type  
2.	Use BFS:
		start from (0,0)  
3.	For each move:
		check:
			- current cell allows direction  
			- neighbor cell allows reverse direction  
4.	Mark visited cells  
5.	If reach (m-1,n-1) → return true  
	Time Complexity
	O(m × n)
	Space Complexity
	O(m × n)
	Solution
class Solution {
public:
    bool hasValidPath(vector<vector<int>>& grid) {
        int m = grid.size();
        int n = grid[0].size();
        // directions: up, down, left, right
        vector<vector<vector<int>>> dirs = {
            {}, // 0 unused
            {{0,-1},{0,1}},      // 1: left-right
            {{-1,0},{1,0}},      // 2: up-down
            {{0,-1},{1,0}},      // 3: left-down
            {{0,1},{1,0}},       // 4: right-down
            {{0,-1},{-1,0}},     // 5: left-up
            {{0,1},{-1,0}}       // 6: right-up
        };
        auto valid = [&](int x, int y){
            return x >= 0 && y >= 0 && x < m && y < n;
        };
        vector<vector<bool>> vis(m, vector<bool>(n, false));
        queue<pair<int,int>> q;
        q.push({0,0});
        vis[0][0] = true;
        while(!q.empty()){
            auto [x,y] = q.front();
            q.pop();
            if(x == m-1 && y == n-1)
                return true;
            for(auto &d : dirs[grid[x][y]]){
                int nx = x + d[0];
                int ny = y + d[1];
                if(!valid(nx,ny) || vis[nx][ny])
                    continue;
                // check reverse connection
                for(auto &back : dirs[grid[nx][ny]]){
                    if(nx + back[0] == x && ny + back[1] == y){
                        vis[nx][ny] = true;
                        q.push({nx,ny});
                        break;
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        return false;
    }
};
	Key Insight
Movement is valid only if:
		both cells agree on connection  
So we must check:
		forward direction + reverse compatibility  
This ensures path is physically valid through streets.
